---

This file pours a 1:1 rum-to-pineapple ratio; Basil Woon's 1928 Kaufman attribution recorded a 2:1 pineapple-forward ratio (two-thirds pineapple, one-third Bacardi).

In a #shaker{} combine @white Cuban-style rum{1.5%oz}, @fresh pineapple juice{1.5%oz}, @grenadine{1%dash}, and @maraschino liqueur{0.25%tsp} (a later refinement) with @cracked ice{1%cup}.
Shake hard until well chilled.
Strain into a chilled #coupe{}.
Garnish with a @maraschino cherry{1}.
